         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">2[5]/3/71 ¶  ¶ When, dear Dr Hooker, are we to get a new general Index to the Botanical Magazine? it is a most helpless affair to work with this grand opus, for not every institution has the rich vote...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">71.03.25b</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Joseph Hooker </p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew correspondence, Australia, Mueller, 1871-81, f. 11.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS annotation: 'recvd. 23/5/71'.</p>
               </note>2[5]/3/71</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>When, dear Dr Hooker, are we to get a new general Index to the Botanical Magazine? it is a most helpless affair to work with this grand opus, for not every institution has the rich votes of Kew to make manuscript catalogues &amp;c. It is always with some hesitation that I approach the Bot Magazine, as it takes so much time to find a thing out, particularly in the volumes issued since Pritzels supplement.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Pritzel (1866). </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Always with </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>best regard</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">I have got now <name key="Dawsonia%20polytrichoides">Dawsonia polytrichoides</name>, from a tropical position 18° S lat. (Rockingham's Bay.)</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Dawsonia%20polytrichoides">Dawsonia polytrichoides</name>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
         </div>
